What were the 'open-door notes'? American diplomats in London received open-door notes from the British government in the form of a memorandum. These notes would offer helpful advice and suggestions to the American diplomats in London, as well as offer advice on UK-US relations. One of the most common open-door notes was the "British Embassy Open Door Note No. XIV of 3 September 1939" which offered suggestions on how to improve US-UK relations.
